6fcb546d2d4ef0c7%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22729%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EUkraine%20has%20attacked%20Russian%20forces%20in%20Crimea%20with%20naval%20drones%20and%20long-range%20missiles.%3Cp%3EVIKTOR%20KOROTAYEV%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22d2bc26cb-7fab-4d99-815d-d74106b0c0a6%5C%22%3ERetaking%20Crimea%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EDespite%20the%20battleground%20challenges%20Ukraine%20faces%2C%20some%20experts%20believe%20it%20could%20retake%20Crimea%20with%20enough%20weapons%2C%20troops%20and%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20would%20involve%20crossing%20the%20Isthmus%20of%20Pereko%2C%20separating%20Crimea%20from%20mainland%20Ukraine%2C%20or%20crossing%20the%20marshes%20to%20the%20east%2C%20called%20Sivash%2C%20to%20reach%20Crimea.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat's%20what%20happened%20during%20World%20War%20II%2C%20when%20the%20Germans%20captured%20Crimea%20in%201942%2C%20and%20the%20Soviets%20recaptured%20it%20in%201944%2C%26quot%3B%20Cancian%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20to%20do%20this%2C%20Ukraine%20first%20needs%20to%20break%20through%20Russia's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fukraine-front-line-forces-fighting-through-russia-surovikin-line-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESuvorikin%20Line%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20complex%20system%20of%20defensive%20fortifications%20and%20obstacles%20across%20Russian-occupied%20territory%20in%20southern%20and%20eastern%20Ukraine%20that%20Ukraine%20has%20never%20pierced%20through.%20A%20force%20that%20advances%20through%20this%20also%20faces%20a%20high%20risk%20of%20becoming%20bottlenecked%20on%20the%20few%20land%20approaches%20and%20destroyed%20by%20the%20short-%20and%20long-range%20firepower%20Russia%20would%20almost%20be%20certain%20to%20bear.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20Sergej%20Sumlenny%2C%20founder%20of%20the%20German%20think%20tank%20European%20Resilience%20Initiative%20Center%2C%20the%20question%20now%20is%20%26quot%3Bwhen%20Ukraine%20will%20accumulate%20so%20much%20firepower%2C%20not%20just%20artillery%2C%20but%20also%20air%20force%2C%20so%20they%20manage%20to%20push%20through%20these%20defensive%20lines%20and%20then%20reach%20the%20operative%20space%26quot%3B%20of%20Crimea.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20and%20when%20Ukrainian%20soldiers%20do%20reach%20Crimea%2C%20Sumlenny%20said%2C%20they%20will%20be%20able%20to%20destroy%20the%20Kerch%20Bridge%20and%20the%20last%20ferry%20road%20over%20the%20Sea%20of%20Azov%2C%20cutting%20off%20all%20of%20Russia's%20supply%20lines%20to%20the%20peninsula%20and%20isolating%20Russian%20forces.%20Using%20long-range%20missiles%20to%20cut-off%20supply%20lines%20was%20a%20crucial%20element%20of%20Ukraine's%20grinding%20and%20successful%20liberation%20of%20the%20city%20of%20Kherson%20in%20late%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESumlenny%20added%20that%20Crimea%20has%20historically%20been%20vulnerable%20to%20offensives.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20is%20no%20case%20in%20history%20when%20anyone%20could%20defend%20Crimea%20from%20an%20attack%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%201921%2C%20the%20Soviet%20Union's%20Red%20Army%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcourses.lumenlearning.com%2Fsuny-hccc-worldhistory2%2Fchapter%2Fthe-russian-civil-war%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecrushed%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20White%20Russians%20and%20took%20control%20of%20the%20peninsula%2C%20and%20in%201941%2C%20the%20Axis%20powers%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.iwm.org.uk%2Fhistory%2Foperation-barbarossa-and-germanys-failure-in-the-soviet-union%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Einvaded%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20Soviet%20Union%20during%20Operation%20Barbarossa%2C%20with%20their%20land%20forces%20laying%20siege%20to%20Sevastopol.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Red%20Army%20launched%20a%20massive%20counter-attack%20in%20late%201943%20with%202.6%20million%20men%20that%20pushed%20the%20Germans%20back%20and%20weakened%20their%20hold%20on%20Crimea.%20After%20two%20and%20a%20half%20years%20of%20German%20occupation%2C%20a%20Soviet%20force%20of%20over%20450%2C000%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.britannica.com%2Fplace%2FCrimea%2FHistory%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eregained%3C%2Fa%3E%20control%20of%20Crimea%20in%201944.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wilsoncenter.org%2Fpublication%2Fwhy-did-russia-give-away-crimea-sixty-years-ago%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etransferred%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20Soviet%20Ukraine%20%E2%80%94%20one%20of%20the%20republics%20of%20the%20Soviet%20Union%20%E2%80%94%20in%201954%2C%20until%20the%20dissolution%20of%20the%20Soviet%20Union%20and%20Ukrainian%20independence%20in%201991.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFinally%2C%20in%202014%2C%20Russian%20forces%20invaded%20and%20occupied%20the%20peninsula%20before%20annexing%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you%20look%20at%20all%20the%20cases%20when%20armies%20were%20clearly%20ready%20to%20fight%20and%20defend%20their%20positions%2C%20we%20can%20say%20that%20Crimea%20is%20practically%20an%20undefendable%20fortress%2C%26quot%3B%20Sumlenny%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSo%2C%20from%20my%20perspective%2C%20the%20moment%20the%20Ukrainian%20army%20will%20appear%20on%20the%20land%20bridge%20%E2%80%94%20the%20Isthmus%20of%20Pereko%20%E2%80%94%20between%20Crimea%20and%20the%20rest%20of%20Ukraine%2C%20the%20Russians%20will%20face%20a%20very%20simple%20choice%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20%26quot%3Beither%20they%20retreat%20immediately%20from%20Crimea%20or%20get%20slaughtered%20or%20captured.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOther%20experts%2C%20however%2C%20struck%20a%20more%20cautious%20tone.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETemnycky%20said%20a%20full-scale%20invasion%20to%20try%20to%20retake%20Crimea%20is%20%26quot%3Bvery%20unlikely%26quot%3B%20due%20to%20the%20huge%20Ukrainian%20losses%20that%20would%20result.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFriedman%2C%20meanwhile%2C%20said%20such%20an%20operation%20would%20require%20a%20%26quot%3Bcataclysmic%20Russian%20collapse%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20he%20said%20is%20%26quot%3Bextremely%20unlikely%20though%20not%20impossible.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIndeed%2C%20there%20have%20been%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fformer-general-warns-russia-nuclear-weapon-stalemate-ukraine-war-2023-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efears%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20Russia%20would%20consider%20nuclear%20force%20if%20its%20troops%20were%20on%20the%20brink%20of%20losing%20Crimea.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECancian%20said%20that%20%26quot%3Bbecause%20of%20its%20difficulty%2C%20retaking%20Crimea%20would%20be%20the%20last%20event%20of%20the%20war%2C%20not%20an%20intermediate%20event.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fukraine-pushed-russian-fleet-out-of-crimea-but-faces-tough-battle-to-retake-it-2024-7%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1722672002000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66a22dffaab37011780a52d3%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fukraine-pushed-russian-fleet-out-of-crimea-but-faces-tough-battle-to-retake-it-2024-7%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Ukraine%20has%20forced%20Russia's%20Black%20Sea%20Fleet%20out%20of%20Crimea%2C%20but%20it%20faces%20an%20uphill%20battle%20to%20retake%20the%20peninsula%2C%20experts%20said.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22tspirlet%40insider.com%20(Thibault%20Spirlet)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fukraine-pushed-russian-fleet-out-of-crimea-but-faces-tough-battle-to-retake-it-2024-7%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Paris%20Olympics%202024%20LIVE%20UPDATES%2C%20Day%208%3A%20Manu%20Bhaker%20finishes%20at%204th%20spot%2C%20misses%20medal%20by%20a%20whisker%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1722671419000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fbsmedia.business-standard.com%2F_media%2Fbs%2Fimg%2